\pard\sb60\sa40\cf1\b\f0\fs44\lang9 FIRE B -- THE ROAD & THE BLEEDING STAIR\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa200\cf3\i Riften gates -> the foot of the 7,000 Steps -> Ivarstead -> the undercroft of High Hrothgar. The campaign's relaunch: one place, one escalating problem, a clean arc with a curtain. ~3 sessions. Self-contained -- run the whole fire from this file.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw20 \sb60\sa220\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 THE SPINE (hold these three lines all module)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 This is an INTRODUCTION.\b0  It ADVANCES threads and RESOLVES nothing personal. Saijah chooses NO patron. Gaelen does NOT die. The crossroads is loaded, never fired.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Frame the objective OUT LOUD as THE RITUAL, never as Gaelen's head.\b0  If they think the mission is 'kill Gaelen,' his escape is a robbery. If they know it is 'stop the Unmaking,' his escape is just Thursday.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Secrets that must hold:\b0  Bjorn's speed reads as REJUVENATION, never Dragonborn (no one can sense a Dragonborn -- not even the Greybeards, who have NO special senses of any kind). Ismara stays unwitnessed by the monastery. The two scout dragons' target stays unknowable.\f1\lang1033  [we may want to prepare a map so we can tell them the direction the dragons are flying off in, a player paying close attention should be able to orient themselves enough to figure out they are heading towards riften.]\f0\lang9\par

\pard\sa140\b Roster on the move:\b0  Davinia (ISMARA fronting -- silver skin), Saijah (bearing ALFONSO the rapier), Orion. Cart: Bjorn, Mila, Esbern (hidden until Scene 1), Nora, GEAR, Ylva, Varon. Animals: Mable (old, dragon-shaken) + the BLACK MARE (fearless warhorse -- sheet: Npcs/the black mare). Krusp & Danica are GONE to Windhelm. \b Everyone climbs\b0  -- Part Two explains why in fiction.\par

\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw20 \sb60\sa220\par

\pard\sb120\sa200\cf1\b\fs40 PART ONE -- THE ROAD\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa200\cf3\i A quiet leg doing three jobs: re-introduce Esbern (comedy + strategy), give the table a breath (respite + personal threads), and teach that the dragons own the sky (the hide). Normal physics the whole way; the first faint time-wrongness only at the very end.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 GM RULES -- "TWO SHADOWS" (the dragon hide)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\box\brdrdash\brdrw15 \li300\ri300\sb40\sa220\b\f2\fs20 THE NOTICE CLOCK -- 6 boxes, starts empty. Not a fight; a hide.\b0\line Two Krosulhah-tier dragons hunt overhead; they tick toward awareness on the\line party's OWN mistakes. 5 COMPLICATION BEATS, each tied to a party asset.\line Responsible character rolls vs an escalating difficulty:\line   Beat 1 Easy(+2) -> Beat 2 Standard(0) -> Beat 3 Hard(-4) -> Beat 4 Hard(-4)\line   -> Beat 5 Very Hard(-6)\line Success: contained, no Notice.   Failure: Notice +1.\line Fumble (nat 20): Notice +2; a dragon banks toward them (next beat one step harder).\line Crit (nat 1): active masking -- Notice -1 (min 0); next beat one step easier.\line PROACTIVE PLAY: every smart move drops the next beat a step or grants Advantage\line (douse fires, still the cart, Orion scouts breathless, Ismara sheathes heat in\line cold, GEAR powers down on permission). Say YES to cleverness.\line FAIL STATE (Notice 6): spotted -> they dive. TELEGRAPH the unwinnability hard\line BEFORE this. If they fight anyway it is a TPK and you warned them.\f0\fs24\par

\pard\sa140\b THE FIVE TELLS:\b0  1) MABLE SPOOKS -- Bjorn rolls (animal handling); the Black Mare in harness beside her = one step EASIER (the fearless horse steadies the frightened one). 2) GEAR HUMS -- Saijah/Orion (Guile); GEAR needs PERMISSION to power down (Cognitorium callback). 3) ALFONSO'S ROT-AURA drifts downwind -- Saijah (bearer); auto-success if she lets Alfonso pull the aura tight through the link. 4) A SMALL HUMAN SOUND (Mila's frightened breath) -- Bjorn or Saijah; comforting her IS the roll. 5) HEAT BLOOM -- Davinia/Ismara can sheathe the cart's warmth in cold -- but using the gift is a quiet temptation (the sweet pull of the power).\f1\lang1033  [with the formating we need to change this a bit, it is confusing which parts are gm pre read and which parts are where the game starts. it needs to be far more visually aparent to the user what goes where, this segmentation will also help ensure that the app parser will work better and help us nail down exactly how formatting will work for that, maybe the above text needs to be smaller and in a differnent font? idk open to suggestion]\f0\lang9\par

