\pard\sb120\sa200\cf1\b\fs40 PART TWO -- IVARSTEAD & THE BLEEDING STAIR\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa200\cf3\i The party's first contact with the Dagon apocalypse and with Gaelen the Root-Twister. Advance, never resolve: the Tower cosmology lands HARD; everything personal stays loaded. Sections: the town -> the ascent -> High Hrothgar -> the undercroft -> the sealing.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 GM RULES -- THE TEMPORAL WEATHER (proximity zones + the alarm)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa140 The distortion is a SIDE EFFECT: the cult corrupts the TOWER from the undercroft; the mountain's existing Time-Wound turns that violence into weather. The cult does not target the Wound and does not control the weather -- they just know how to surf it.\par

\pard\box\brdrdash\brdrw15 \li300\ri300\sb40\sa220\b\f2\fs20 HOW IT RUNS (core, locked):\b0\line 1. The GM sets a REAL-WORLD ALARM (phone, hidden). It fires with NO warning;\line    the players learn to dread the sound.\line 2. On the alarm: GM rolls d20 -> picks which table in the CURRENT ZONE's set is\line    active ('the weather shifts'). Announce nothing but the sensation.\line 3. In combat, every character rolls d20 TEMPO at the start of their turn on the\line    active table -> that is their action economy this turn.\line 4. THE GRADIENT = two dials: higher zones have NASTIER tables AND the alarm\line    fires MORE OFTEN.\line 5. SEPARATION IS EXPOSURE: anyone who strays from the group slips out of the\line    shared 'now' -- they face this zone's weather ALONE, no one to pull them\line    back into sequence. A tight, roped body is the only anchor.\line\line\b ENEMIES CHEAT:\b0  Dagonites carry grafted TIDE-SHARDS (obsidian slivers fused\line at the sternum) -- they choose their Tempo result instead of rolling. THE\line COUNTER: destroy the shard -- a Called Shot (Very Hard -6), or Sunder aimed at\line it, or it shatters on their death -- and that cultist rolls like everyone else.\line Ylva FEELS every cheat as a broken hunt-rhythm (hackles, growl) before any\line mortal can name it.\f0\fs24\par
\b\f2\fs20 ZONE TABLES (d20 TEMPO -- roll at start of each combat turn)\b0\line\line ZONE 0 -- THE TOWN (faintest; alarm ~every 25 min real time)\line   1 Frozen (0 actions) | 2-4 Dragging (Major OR Minor) | 5-16 In step (normal)\line   | 17-19 Quickened (+1 Minor) | 20 Unmoored (full extra turn after this one)\line   Social distortion instead of combat weather: see Scene 8's card.\line\line ZONE 1 -- THE LOWER STEPS, Waystones 1-2 (alarm ~15 min)\line   1-2 Frozen | 3-5 Dragging | 6-15 In step | 16-19 Quickened | 20 Unmoored\line\line ZONE 2 -- THE UPPER STEPS, Waystone 3 -> High Hrothgar (alarm ~10 min)\line   1-3 Frozen | 4-7 Dragging | 8-13 In step | 14-18 Quickened | 19-20 Unmoored\line\line ZONE 3 -- THE UNDERCROFT (worst; alarm ~6 min)\line   1-4 Frozen | 5-8 Dragging | 9-12 In step | 13-17 Quickened | 18-20 Unmoored\line   PLUS: any natural 1 or 20 on Tempo ALSO triggers a SECONDARY HORROR (d20):\line    1-4  your spell/attack this turn resolves at the START of your NEXT turn\line    5-8  damage you deal this turn already landed LAST round (retroactive; if the\line         target acted since, it staggers them now instead)\line    9-12 echo-step: you are suddenly 15 ft from where you stood (GM places you\line         where you were 1 round ago)\line    13-16 doubled: act twice this turn, then LOSE your next turn entirely\line    17-20 the initiative order reshuffles (reroll all) at this turn's end\f0\fs24\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  The zone tables and secondary-horror list are built to the locked dials (scratch 5); adjust freely at the table -- the ALARM and the DREAD are the mechanic, the numbers are servants.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 GM RULES -- SAIJAH'S DOUBLE MIGRAINE\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\box\brdrdash\brdrw15 \li300\ri300\sb40\sa220\b\f2\fs20 THE DOUBLE MIGRAINE (triggers the instant she touches the first black sap)\b0\line Two Towers scream at once: the Eldergleam she always feels + the Throat under\line fresh assault. While anywhere in the corrupted zone (the whole Stair):\line    -2 Guile   |   -2 Agility   |   +2 damage taken from all sources\line Sustained and brutal BY DESIGN -- the player must FEEL it, because that ache is\line exactly what gives Hircine's 'I can make it stop' its hook (Scene 11).\line (Replaces the -1 city penalty here.)\f0\fs24\par

\pard\sb280\sa40\cf1\b\fs40 8   THE FOOT OF THE STAIR -- Ivarstead is the bottom edge of the unmaking\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa220\cf3\i Set-piece + social. The frightened half-empty town, the first Waystone, the inn that is not a haven. ZONE 0.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb80\sa60\cf6\b\fs26 >> READ ALOUD\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li600\ri400\sa220\cf6\i "Ivarstead is a handful of grey houses pressed against the biggest thing in the world. Half of them stand with their doors open on emptied rooms -- packed in a hurry, gone. Smoke rises from three chimneys. A barricade of farm carts and fence posts blocks the lane toward the river, manned by nobody.\line\line At the bridge, the first Waystone leans in its socket, and it is bleeding: a slow black sap crawling UP the carved stone, against gravity, pooling in the old runes until they read wet and dark. Where a drop falls, it falls slowly -- slower than it should, like it is falling through deeper water than the world's.\line\line A big man sits on the inn's steps with a loaded pack at his feet -- packed for the climb he has not made. He watches you come in the way a man watches the first help arrive at a fire that has already taken the roof."\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sa140\b KLIMMEK:\b0  "You came. Gods -- somebody came." (a breath, steadying) "I still have the supplies for the monastery. Been packed nine days. Every time I set foot past the third stone something... happens to the walk. Hours go by that I don't remember walking. Once I came down and my beard had grown out three days. The masters are up there ALONE, and I can't -- I can't make the climb." He pushes the pack toward you. "You're climbing. I know you are. Take it. Please."\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  SAIJAH -- STATION 1 fires at the Waystone: the black sap NAGS -- familiar, can't place it. An itch, not a recognition. (The DOUBLE MIGRAINE fires the instant she TOUCHES it -- debuff card ON for the rest of the Stair.) Davinia's Sight: the corruption reads as a structured working running DOWN into the mountain's root, not spilling up from the stone.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 THE TOWN'S BROKEN TIME (Zone 0 -- social, not lethal)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\box\brdrdash\brdrw15 \li300\ri300\sb40\sa220\b\f2\fs20 TOWN DISTORTION (color any conversation with one of these; light touch):\b0\line - An answer arrives BEFORE the question finishes being asked.\line - A villager repeats the last exchange verbatim, unaware; it plays like an echo.\line - Someone thanks the party for a thing they have not done yet.\line - A door is heard closing a full breath before it visibly closes.\line In fights here: Zone 0 Tempo, alarm rare. The horror is social first.\f0\fs24\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 NO HAVEN AT THE FOOT (the everyone-climbs logic -- play it, don't announce it)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2\b0 The corruption is creeping DOWN into the streets, and Dagonites move through the empty half of town after dark. There is nowhere safe to leave a child, an old man, or a horse.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 If they shelter at the inn\b0  (the least-bad option): it is ATTACKED in the night -- Dagonites and a shard-grafted zealot, torches, the Kvatch register: this is what Dagon taking a space looks like. People are hurt. The horse must come INSIDE (the mare, fearless, walks in like she has always lived indoors). Anything left OUTSIDE is destroyed or taken.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 The lesson the fiction teaches:\b0  to wait below is to wait inside the thing they came to stop. Bjorn will not be parted from Mila; the party will not abandon either of them; and on the mountain, the weather ISOLATES stragglers. The whole crew climbs as one -- guarding their two most precious people up a mountain of cosmic horror.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 THE ENEMY -- DAGONITES (Expert-tier per the master table)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\box\brdrdash\brdrw15 \li300\ri300\sb40\sa220\b\f2\fs20 DAGONITE CULTIST  x4-8  (TL1, Expert)\b0  -- razor-scarred, ash-grey robes\line HP 100  |  Dmg 20 (jagged glass-steel)  |  DR 11  |  17/15/13/8 (P=Might or Magic)\line Tide-shard graft: CHOOSES Tempo (see weather card) until the shard is destroyed.\line Fights to the end; retreat is not in the liturgy.\line\line\b SHARD ZEALOT  (TL2, Expert)\b0  -- the graft has spread up the throat; voice doubles\line HP 250  |  Dmg 31  |  DR 17  |  18/16/13/8 (P=Magic)\line Casts Ash Shell (4 FP) and Firebolt (3 FP, 6 dmg) between blade-work.\line Cheats Tempo; on its death the shard bursts -- 5 dmg to all within 5 ft.\f0\fs24\par

\pard\sb100\sa240\cf1\b EXIT ->\cf2\b0  Dawn after the inn night. Klimmek's pack on someone's shoulders. The first of seven thousand steps.   \b -> 9  THE BLEEDING STEPS\b0\par

\pard\sb280\sa40\cf1\b\fs40 9   THE BLEEDING STEPS -- the ascent\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa220\cf3\i ZONES 1-2. Waystone by Waystone the world comes loose. Dagonite ambushes that cheat. Saijah stations 2-4. Keep the rope tight.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb80\sa60\cf6\b\fs26 >> READ ALOUD\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li600\ri400\sa220\cf6\i "The Steps are older than any road you have walked -- worn hollow in the middle by seven thousand years of pilgrims -- and they climb out of the valley in long switchbacks that vanish into cloud. Every few hundred steps a Waystone stands in its socket, and every one of them is bleeding the same slow black sap, the runes drowned dark.\line\line At the first stone the snow around your boots falls UPWARD for three heartbeats, a soft reversed flurry, and settles as if nothing happened. By the third stone your own voices start coming back off the rock faces a moment too late. By the fourth, you walk beside your own afterimages -- a half-second echo of each of you, following a half-step behind."\cf2\i0\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  ZONE 1 through Waystone 2; ZONE 2 from Waystone 3 up. Run the alarm honestly -- the dread of the sound is the mechanic. ROPE RULE out loud once: stay together; anyone who strays faces the weather alone (separation = the Zone's Tempo with nobody to pull you back).\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 SAIJAH -- STATIONS 2-4 (paced, never a lecture)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Station 2 (deeper):\b0  she PLACES the signature -- "I've felt this before" (Thornheart; the Solitude temple tree) -- but reads it as coincidence. Two points, no pattern.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Station 3:\b0  the migraine DOUBLES -- two simultaneous sources, which makes no sense to her. The -2/-2/+2 is fully on. Something is deeply wrong; she does not know what.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Station 4 (Gaelen's voice -- through the corrupted leylines, to her alone, mid-climb):\b0  warm, sincere, reasonable: "You feel it as pain because you were taught the cage is your body. Forests that burn and regrow in a breath. Beasts that never stop becoming. I am not breaking anything, little sentinel. I am opening a door that was nailed shut before you were born." -- and the SCALE slips: "...prisons. I have been opening them for years. This is not the first, or the last." A clue she cannot yet hold.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 COMBAT -- THE CHEATED GAME (Dagonite ambushes)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  Use CULTISTS + a ZEALOT per ambush (cards, Scene 8). They surf the weather: stolen turns, doubled moves, strikes out of sequence -- while the party rolls Tempo. Make the unfairness VISIBLE. Then let the party break the shards and even the game -- that reversal is the fun.\par

\pard\sa140\b YLVA -- THE REFEREE'S WRATH (this develops SAIJAH, not Ylva):\b0  the first time a cultist cheats, Ylva's hackles rise BEFORE it happens -- she growls at empty air a half-second early, then the cheat comes. She cannot name 'temporal weather'; she knows a FOUL happened. "They're cheating. The hunt has RULES." Her fury is theological -- the laws make the game sacred; these people spit on the game itself. Saijah, watching, is seeing the exact hunt-rhythm sense Hircine could one day give HER. \b VARON\b0  agrees from the opposite pole -- Shadowscale doctrine kills clean INSIDE time's rules -- and the two who cannot stand each other fight back to back, aligned. Give it one beat out loud.\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  BJORN: his speed may FLICKER again on the climb if Mila is threatened -- shorter than the road flare, still read as rejuvenation, never named. NORA (if a player pulled her up rather than cart-side... she climbs -- everyone does): the broken time does something WRONG to her two black gems -- her parents' souls flickering, stuttering, DOUBLING. A horror beat, not a resolution. ALFONSO: what does a mountain of broken time do to a soul living in iron? Let the sword be uneasy -- a wrongness he will not explain.\par

\pard\sb100\sa240\cf1\b EXIT ->\cf2\b0  The last switchback. Grey stone walls in the cloud. The monastery.   \b -> 10  HIGH HROTHGAR\b0\par

\pard\sb280\sa40\cf1\b\fs40 10   HIGH HROTHGAR -- the quarantine of the masters\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa220\cf3\i Character scene at the top of the world. The TOWER hard-reveal, Kynareth's first new word in years, and the Ring feeding it all to Solitude.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb80\sa60\cf6\b\fs26 >> READ ALOUD\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li600\ri400\sa220\cf6\i "The monastery is grey stone against grey sky, and the doors stand barred from within. When they open -- slowly, to Klimmek's pack and your knock -- the man inside has a face like a starved hawk and hands that tremble with something past exhaustion. Behind him, in the great cold hall, three more grey-robed figures sit in a triangle around a brazier, and the air between them HUMS -- a note below hearing, steady as a heartbeat, that you feel in your teeth and the floor and the old stone walls.\line\line They are not meditating. They are HOLDING something. You can feel the mountain trying to shake itself apart beneath you, gentled -- barely -- by the hum."\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sa140\b MASTER ARNGEIR\b0  (voice cracked from disuse and overuse at once): "You climbed through THAT. Then you have seen what is happening to the mountain." (he looks at the pack, and something in the hawk face almost breaks) "...Klimmek's bread. Forgive me. It has been -- some time."\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 WHAT THE MASTERS GIVE (scholarship, not senses)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 THE HARD REVEAL -- the word TOWER:\b0  "You stand on one of the pillars of the world. The Throat is a TOWER -- one of the stones that holds Mundus against Oblivion. The zealots below are not desecrating a holy place. They are cutting a load-bearing wall of the WORLD. The shaking you feel in time is the Tower beginning to fail." -> The party LEAVES KNOWING they are in the main plot. Land it plainly.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 The Way of the Voice OPENS:\b0  the masters accept the party as the first help to reach them; the door stands open hereafter (scholarship, Word Wall locations for seekers -- the masters themselves cannot shout offensively enough to leave; holding the mountain takes everything they have).\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 What they CANNOT do (hold this line):\b0  no special senses of ANY kind. They do not see Ismara in Davinia. They do not sense anything in Bjorn. They cannot name a Dragonborn -- no one can. They hold the summit by Voice and endurance, and they are losing.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 The geography clue:\b0  "The working is BELOW us -- in the undercroft, at the mountain's root. The summit path is SEALED (only a Shout clears it, and none of us can be spared from the holding). Whatever you came to stop, you will find it downstairs."\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 KYNARETH'S REVEAL (Saijah -- station 5; the goddess, NOT the masters)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  At Kyne's own peak, the goddess finally gives Saijah something NEW -- cryptic, non-verbal, the first fresh thing after all the repeated instructions. An IMAGE she cannot decode: a wind carrying a great soul upward -- toward a hall of mist and warriors -- and the certainty, wordless and enormous, that her ENDURING matters to the end of the world. Somewhere in the image, unnamed, a shape like a big man standing between a child and the sky. She gets a FEELING about Bjorn, never a label. This is the reason to endure the pain -- delivered the night BEFORE Hircine offers to end it.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 THE OTHERS AT THE MONASTERY\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 DAVINIA/ISMARA:\b0  her Sight is the only thing that can READ the Tower -- the leyline lattice, the corruption's shape crawling the root. A Sight showcase. And ISMARA'S TEMPTATION: amid the breaking time she offers to FREEZE the wound locally -- stasis against chaos, tactically real, self-corrupting. \b Using it advances the CDI.\b0  Offer it once, cleanly, and let the player choose. (The masters see none of this.)\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 ORION -- the tonal architect:\b0  the corruption is a FREQUENCY phenomenon and he is the one person equipped to read it as MECHANISM. Diagnostic Song against the hum: he maps the working's structure (this feeds Scene 11's disruption options and his Severance research) and earns the masters' respect as a fellow student of tone -- a real tie, a real spotlight. THE GUT-PUNCH (GM-only, say nothing): the Ring has fed Valerius the entire apocalypse, live, all climb.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 GEAR\b0  (he climbed; everyone climbs): quantifies the break -- "local causality variance exceeds Dwemer tonal tolerances by a factor of nine. I have no protocol for this. I find I do not enjoy that." Pairs with Orion. Light.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 ESBERN:\b0  among the masters' books like a starving man at a feast -- and the one who says the OTHER quiet part: "The Wall shows a council of heroes when the Dragonborn fails. It never shows what holds the SKY up while they argue. Now we know."\par

\pard\sb100\sa240\cf1\b EXIT ->\cf2\b0  Down the inner stair. The hum fades above; something older hums below.   \b -> 11  THE UNDERCROFT\b0\par

\pard\sb280\sa40\cf1\b\fs40 11   THE RITUAL IN THE UNDERCROFT -- Gaelen at the root\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa220\cf3\i The boss. ZONE 3 -- the worst weather. Objective: DISRUPT THE RITUAL. Gaelen escapes by design; Jasper does not.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb80\sa60\cf6\b\fs26 >> READ ALOUD\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li600\ri400\sa220\cf6\i "The undercroft is older than the monastery above it -- a vaulted root-cellar of the world, columns of living rock running down into dark that breathes. The Dagonites have made it a garden. Red light comes up out of carved channels in the floor, all of them running inward to a central well where the mountain's root stands exposed: a column of something older than stone, and INTO it, like ivy into a wall, black sap-lines are growing upward from an array of obsidian shards arranged in a blooming spiral.\line\line A Bosmer moves through the array unhurried, crimson chitin catching the light, one arm a grafted mass of charred heartwood and obsidian that gestures at things he is not looking at. He is adjusting each shard with the care of a man tuning an instrument he loves.\line\line Without turning, in a voice that is warm and genuinely pleased: 'Oh -- visitors. Good. I hoped the mountain would manage to be heard. Come in, come in. You are not interrupting; nothing can interrupt this. But company is rare, and I have wanted to meet you for the longest time.'"\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 GAELEN -- HOW HE PLAYS (unsettling, never evil)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2\b0 The warm, sincere, reasonable CENTER of an apocalypse. He talks like an ally trying to get compatriots to stop suffering for a stagnant world: the Aedra gave mortals a CELL -- linear time, fragile flesh; Dagon offers the KEY; the Unmaking is HEALING.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 THE QUIET WISH (plant it -- overheard when he thinks no one listens, to no one):\b0  "I want it to be perfect. Please... let it be perfect." Not a plea, not a crack in a mask -- the closest thing his altered architecture has to hope. Every projection the players make onto it will be slightly wrong. He should leave the table unable to dismiss him.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 THE YLVA EXCHANGE (give both liturgies one beat, out loud):\b0  GAELEN: "Rules are the bars, hunter. I am unbending them." YLVA (shaking with a fury even she cannot name): "The rules are what make the hunt HOLY. Prey runs, hunter chases, the fastest wins -- that is the whole church. You are not freeing anything. You are pissing on the game." The most theologically serious person in the room about why the Unmaking is wrong is the werewolf.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 ALFONSO -- the duel only he can have:\b0  Gaelen speaks HIS language -- entropy. Peryite's pestilence is decay WITH order, a cycle that feeds the world; Gaelen's Unmaking is decay as pure negation, death that feeds NOTHING. Let Alfonso be almost-tempted -- then articulate exactly why it is blasphemy. Quiet horror: how close his own philosophy sits to the abyss.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 HIRCINE'S TEMPTATION (Saijah -- station 6 in the doorway of the boss)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  Just before or during the fight, the Hunter's voice -- the morning after Kynareth finally spoke: "Little sentinel. That noise in your skull. I can make it STOP." He is not lying. THE HIDDEN COST he simply does not mention: the channel that screams is the same channel the goddess speaks through -- silence the pain and you silence KYNARETH (the Mzinchaleft principle: silence is not always peace). NO weredog offer, NO choice resolved here -- the senses may sharpen a moment (a taste), and the offer HANGS. If the player accepts outright anyway, do not block it -- but that is her player firing the crossroads early, not the module.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 THE FIGHT -- DISRUPT THE WORKING\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa140\b Frame it out loud (again): the objective is the RITUAL.\b0  The spiral array feeds the sap-lines into the root. Break enough of it and the working collapses. Gaelen defends the work, not himself; Jasper defends GAELEN.\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 THE ARRAY:\b0  5 anchor-shards (obsidian, waist-high). Each: \b 25 HP, DR 10\b0  -- or a \b Hard Might (-4)\b0  wrench to topple one bodily, or Orion's tonal counter-note (\b Hard Magic -4\b0 , guided by his Scene 10 mapping) to crack one at range. Every anchor down weakens the weather one step in here (Zone 3 -> 2 -> 1...); at THREE down the working is DISRUPTED (win condition); all five down = staunched as clean as this ever gets.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 THE WEATHER FIGHTS EVERYONE\b0  (Zone 3 card, alarm ~6 min): the cultists cheat it, the party endures it, and every anchor destroyed evens the game a step -- the mechanical arc IS the story arc.\par

\pard\box\brdrdash\brdrw15 \li300\ri300\sb40\sa220\b\f2\fs20 GAELEN THE ROOT-TWISTER (Apex Villain -- full sheet: Npcs/new mythic dawn leader)\b0\line Magic 21 (cannot fail a Magic roll)  Agility 17  Guile 15  Might 8\line HP 40 (Paradise Mantle: regen -- outheal or shut off)  |  FP 35  |  DR 22 (23 vs spells)\line Mythic Dawn chitin skin; Daedric graft-arm acts on its own initiative.\line HE IS NOT HERE TO DIE: at disruption (3 anchors down) he PHASES -- the collapsing\line weather releases his half-untimed soul and he falls back to the Eldergleam plan.\line If somehow cornered before that, he spends everything to phase early.\line\line\b JASPER AVALON (lieutenant -- ~AP 10 character build; he does NOT retreat)\b0\line Dunmer mage, THE ATRONACH. Might 4  Agility 6  Magic 19  Guile 12\line HP 9 (glass -- his defense is absorption and ash)  |  FP 16  |  DR 8 (Ebonyflesh up)\line SPELL ABSORPTION (Atronach stone): once per combat, negates a hostile spell\line and regains its FP cost.  Ancestor's Wrath (Dunmer): 1/adventure fire aura.\line Casts: Incinerate (9 FP, 12 dmg) | Ash Shell (4 FP, Might roll or encased 2 rds)\line | Ash Rune (10 FP) | Lightning Bolt (3 FP). Tide-shard graft: cheats Tempo.\line FIGHTS TO THE END defending the ritual space. Dies here. One-and-done.\f0\fs24\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 THE JASPER REVEAL (via Gaelen -- this is how the consent lands loud)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa140 When a party member recognizes the Dunmer (Davinia's player above all -- this weight is aimed at HER), \b GAELEN\b0  (mild, without pausing his work): "It seems you were familiar with this vessel... that is unfortunate, for he is gone. As for his flesh -- he gave it to the Dawn." Jasper was a secret Dagon devotee IN LIFE -- a lone worshipper, long before he died in the Pale Lady's tomb. Nothing was stolen. If the party tries to TALK to him, he CAN speak -- and what he says is worse than silence: he is content. The empty, discarded man was told his emptiness was HOLY, and he gave himself gladly, because it was the first time anything ever wanted him.\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  VICTIM vs WILLING is the differentiator from the Echo: Kyboh was stolen (rage FOR him); Jasper GAVE himself (nothing to save). Do not soften either half.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf4\b\fs26 GAELEN'S ESCAPE (at 3 anchors down -- run it exactly)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sb80\sa60\cf6\b\fs26 >> READ ALOUD\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li600\ri400\sa220\cf6\i "The third anchor cracks and the whole undercroft LURCHES -- the red light guttering, the sap-lines withering back out of the root like ivy burned at the stem. Gaelen watches it happen with his head tilted, the way a man watches weather ruin a picnic.\line\line 'Hm. Unfinished, then.' He looks at you -- genuinely, unhurriedly interested. 'You finally showed up. Do you know, I had begun to think no one was coming, all these years. How wonderful. Something new.'\line\line The broken time reaches for him and he steps INTO it, the way you would step into a doorway -- and he is a half-second behind himself, and then a full second, and then he is an afterimage the room forgets to keep."\cf2\i0\par

\pard\li360\sa140\cf1\b GM:\cf2\b0  He falls back to the ELDERGLEAM -- the primary plan the party has never touched, still running perfectly. They did not beat him; they interrupted a man who reached for a second prize. He recurs with a grievance now attached -- curious, not vengeful. Scarier.\par

\pard\sb100\sa240\cf1\b EXIT ->\cf2\b0  The weather stills. The mountain stops shaking. It is not healed.   \b -> 12  THE SEALING & THE COST\b0\par

\pard\sb280\sa40\cf1\b\fs40 12   THE SEALING & THE COST -- staunched, not sealed\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\sa220\cf3\i The curtain. Rewards, the seeds that finish growing AFTER, and the doors this module opens.\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb80\sa60\cf6\b\fs26 >> READ ALOUD\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\li600\ri400\sa220\cf6\i "The masters come down the inner stair when the shaking stops -- slowly, holding the walls, men walking after weeks at an oar. Arngeir stands a long time at the wounded root, where the black lines have withered to scars in the stone.\line\line 'Staunched,' he says at last. 'A cut finger, bound. The body of the thing that attacked this mountain is still out there, and still working.' He looks at each of you in turn, and bows -- the full bow, to all of you. 'The Way of the Voice is open to you. It is a small thing to offer the people who held up the sky. It is what we have.'"\cf2\i0\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 REWARDS\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 1 AP each\b0  (a full fire completed) -- plus dragon-kill AP if any dragon somehow died this module (it should not have).\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 The Way of the Voice:\b0  High Hrothgar open as sanctuary + scholarship; the masters know WHERE Word Walls are for specific shouts a seeker might want (they cannot shout them; reference, not power).\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Loot:\b0  the zealots' tide-shards (inert now -- but Nora or Ismara will want them badly: crystallized wrong-time, priceless to a researcher and mildly unwholesome to carry). Klimmek's gratitude and Ivarstead's -- the town half-returns as word spreads the mountain has quieted.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 SEEDS PLANTED (they finish growing AFTER the module -- do not harvest early)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Saijah's realization (station 7, ON THE ROAD OUT, days later):\b0  gildergreens + the Throat + the word TOWER + TWO migraines finally assemble -- one tree, it is a Tower, TWO Towers are under attack, and there is a HEART she has never found. The module plants; the realization grows. Let her player say it first if they get there.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 The heart-hunt -> DANICA:\b0  the true Eldergleam's location is the chosen sisters' deepest secret (a women's mystery -- no man may ever know). Three living sisters: Danica, one in Whiterun (cold to the Lanterns -- Danica's letters made the party the temple's cautionary tale), one visiting Solitude. The road to the cure runs through the reconciliation. The braid is now load-bearing.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 The two cure-routes (set up, never forced):\b0  KYNARETH -- heal the heart (needs Danica). HIRCINE -- no Danica needed at all: the Alpha and the cull. If reconciliation looks impossible, Hircine's road becomes the shortcut priced in Saijah's soul.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Node-saving (the standing open door):\b0  every gildergreen node is SAVEABLE; the party has simply kept not going. From here on, offer node-defense chances on the road; the Solitude node (slow, strong, a chosen sister already present) is the best first savable win.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Valerius knows everything\b0  the Ring saw -- the Tower, the apocalypse, the party's capabilities. File it; spend it later.\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Gaelen, unfinished:\b0  "you finally showed up." The Eldergleam campaign continues off-screen. He is curious about them now. That is worse.\par

\pard\sb160\sa70\cf5\b\fs26 CONSEQUENCE LEDGER (what the OTHER fires did while they climbed)\cf2\b0\fs24\par

\pard\fi-280\li500\sa120\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Fire A (Krusp & Danica at Windhelm):\b0  rumor arrives -- the plague fought to a standstill at a cost. Danica's cough, when they finally hear her again, has teeth in it. [Attrition canon: her lungs.]\par
\cf5\b\bullet\tab\cf2 Fire C (ignored -- Bleak Falls):\b0  Antoine rebuilds unobserved on top of the Dragonstone. The 6-8 week Strain 2.0 clock RUNS. Esbern says the Dragonstone line again on the road out. He will keep saying it.\par

\pard\sb100\sa240\cf1\b EXIT ->\cf2\b0  The cart rolls down out of the grey hills with the mountain quiet behind it -- and the Dragonstone pressure, the Dirge reckoning, and the road to Bleak Falls ahead.   \b -> NEXT MODULE: FIRE C / BLEAK FALLS\b0\par
}
